Polar Grid structure for Three Way Polar Plot

Source: R/polar_grid.R
polar_grid.Rd

This function creates polar grid of radius r

polar_grid(r_vector, axis_ticks, axis_angle = 4/3, ...)

Arguments

r_vector

numerical vector of radial coordinates
axis_ticks

a numerical vector of breaks for the radial axis
axis_angle

Angle to position the radial axis in pi (default = 4/3)
...

optional parameters for pretty

Value

Returns a list containing:

  • 'polar_grid' The coordinates for a radial grid

  • 'axes' The axes features for plotly

  • 'axis_labels' The axis labels

  • 'r' The grid radius

  • 'text_coords' The coordinates for text labels

References

Lewis, Myles J., et al. (2019). "Molecular portraits of early rheumatoid arthritis identify clinical and treatment response phenotypes. Cell reports, 28:9

Examples

polar_grid(r_vector = 1:10, axis_ticks = 1:10)
